ZH: 我们的谈话突然岔开，变成了别的话题。
EN: Our conversation suddenly veered off and became about something else.

ZH: 孩子在教堂门口岔开去玩了。
EN: The child veered off to play at the entrance of the church.

ZH: 他岔开了主题，开始讲他上个周末的旅行。
EN: He deviated from the topic and started talking about his weekend trip.

ZH: 会议进行到一半时，讨论岔开了。
EN: During the meeting, the discussion veered off halfway through.

ZH: 在讨论问题时，他有时候会岔开一些有趣的话题。
EN: When discussing issues, he sometimes veers off into interesting topics.

ZH: 他总是喜欢岔开话题，无法集中精力。
EN: He always likes to change the subject and can't concentrate.

ZH: 和他讨论这个问题时，我们岔开了。
EN: We got sidetracked when discussing this issue with him.

ZH: 她岔开了关于家庭的话题，开始谈论她的工作。
EN: She veered away from the topic of family and started talking about her work.

ZH: 我试图回答他的问题，但他总是岔开话题。
EN: I tried to answer his question, but he always changed the subject.

ZH: 不要岔开话题，我们需要集中讨论这个问题。
EN: Do not deviate from the subject; we need to focus on discussing this issue.

ZH: 他在演讲中经常会岔开话题，导致观众感到困惑。
EN: He often veers off topic in his speeches, which confuses the audience.

ZH: 他会有意地岔开话题，以避免回答棘手的问题。
EN: He deliberately changes the subject to avoid answering difficult questions.

ZH: 我们应该避免岔开辩论的关键问题。
EN: We should avoid deviating from the key issues in the debate.

ZH: 在辩论中讨论的问题岔开时，很难再回到正题。
EN: It is difficult to get back to the main point when the discussed issue veers off during a debate.

ZH: 我们不应该岔开谈论环境保护的重要性。
EN: We shouldn't veer off discussing the importance of environmental protection.

ZH: 请认真回答我的问题，不要岔开。
EN: Please answer my question seriously, without sidetracking.

ZH: 这个会议岔开了，我们需要重新聚焦。
EN: This meeting has deviated; we need to refocus.

ZH: 岔开的话题会使我们的讨论变得混乱。
EN: Sidetracked topics can make our discussion chaotic.

ZH: 不要岔开，我们还没有解决这个问题。
EN: Don't wander off; we haven't resolved this issue yet.

ZH: 我感到沮丧，因为我们总是岔开需要解决的议题。
EN: I feel frustrated because we always veer off the topics that need to be resolved.
